### <a name="update"></a> About Updating to Ops Manager v1.7.15 or Later

If you are currently on Ops Manager v1.7.14 or earlier, you should update your Ops Manager.
Later versions include a major stemcell upgrade to 3233.x. This stemcell uses the Linux kernel v4.4 instead of the v3.19.
Ubuntu is no longer providing CVE patches for Linux kernel v3.19.

